  "poem": {
    "content": "A digital fog, a frozen aspect gleaned,\nThe general feeling of a world unseen.\nPrepare the lab, for echoes faint and low,\nWhere icy lizard dreams begin to flow.\n\nRetreat into cushions, softly deep,\nWhile frosted windows secrets keep.\nAgain, the shadow lengthens on the wall,\nAs digital material starts to fall.\n\nOppose the chill, the creeping, icy dread,\nDecorate with warmth, though hope feels dead.\nAfford the fire, let the embers gleam,\nA fragile island in a frozen dream.\n\nThe aspect shifts, the fog begins to lift,\nA lizard’s eye reveals an offered gift.\nAnd though the general mood is stark and wan,\nPrepare, retreat, let warmth be born again.",
